𝐅𝐀𝐂𝐄 𝐂𝐎𝐕𝐄𝐑𝐈𝐍𝐆 𝐅𝐀𝐐: We have received a number of questions regarding what constitutes an acceptable face covering for school. 𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐝𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐫𝐢𝐜𝐭 𝐰𝐢𝐥𝐥 𝐩𝐫𝐨𝐯𝐢𝐝𝐞 𝐚 𝐧𝐨-𝐜𝐨𝐬𝐭 𝐦𝐚𝐬𝐤 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐚 𝐧𝐞𝐜𝐤 𝐠𝐚𝐢𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐞𝐚𝐜𝐡 𝐬𝐭𝐮𝐝𝐞𝐧𝐭.

Families may also provide their own face covering, which should meet CDC guidelines of being two-layer cloth. Masks with openings, such as mesh masks, masks with valves, or masks with holes of any kind are not considered acceptable face coverings.

post_text: Keep an eye out for Rooted Bucks at our food sites tomorrow, June 19th! This is a great way to #eathealthy and #supportlocal.
shared_text:
Project Rooted
June 18 at 10:23 AM ·

Great food, with real local flavor can be found right in your own community.

We invite you to join us in our newest program launch, Rooted Bucks, an opportunity to enjoy edible eats at our local farmers markets. The Rooted Bucks will be available tomorrow, June 19th, at local lunch sites for kids including Dubuque Community School District Sites, Holy Ghost, Boys and Girls Club(dinner service), West Dubuque Lunch sites, and Resources Unite!

Rooted Bucks are redeemable for vegetables, fruits, whole grain breads, meat, cheese and eggs, herbs and food producing plants, syrups and honey!

We Invite you to continue to share your Rooted Experiences with us using #myrootedproject.

May 2 at 8:35 AM ·

City of Dubuque Government
April 26 at 12:16 PM ·

The IDPH was notified of 384 additional positive cases of COVID-19 in Iowa, including an additional 10 cases in Dubuque County. Six more people with COVID-19 in Iowa have died, bringing the statewide total to 118.

Iowa now has a total of 5,476 positive cases and Dubuque County has 80. The new cases in Dubuque County were six adults, three middle-aged adults, and one older adult.

Positive cases identified in Iowa and Dubuque County are expected to continue to increase as more testing is completed, additional surveillance testing of large businesses and long-term care facilities continues, and additional Test Iowa sites are opened.

According to IDPH, 36,090 Iowans have been tested, 286 are currently hospitalized, and 1,900 Iowans have recovered. For additional details, visit https://coronavirus.iowa.gov/

Stay Home, Stay Safe, and Take the Test Iowa Assessment at www.testiowa.com

post_text: Tonight, and for the past 2 weeks, Dalzell Field joined other high school stadiums across the state to #lightupIA by flipping the light switch. Every minute the lights shine will signify a day lost during the spring sports season due to the Covid-19 pandemic. The lights turn on at 8:20 pm in honor of the 2020 Class and will turn off at 8:45 pm.

National Mississippi River Museum & Aquarium
April 22 at 3:41 PM ·

We were so fortunate to team up with the Dubuque Community School District to distribute 350 Eastern White Pine saplings, native wildflower seeds, and at home nature activities to hundreds of families in our community. If that's not an Earth Day celebration to remember, we don't know what is!

A big thank you to Wagner Nursery Inc. for donating the tree saplings and to 1 Mississippi, The Association of Zoos and Aquariums, and the Disney Conservation Fund for funding all other materials.

🌎💚 Happy Earth Day! 💚🌎

#Rivers4Earth, #EarthDay2020, #PartyForThePlanet #WeAreAZA #SpringIntoAction

"We speak for the very least of our brothers and sisters. Not because we have the power to do so. Not because we have the position and privilege to do so. Because our lives are more complete."

December 2, 2019 at 9:30 AM ·

#MakeADifferenceMonday

shared_text:
Dubuque Symphony Orchestra
November 8, 2019 at 12:09 PM ·

Today we welcome area 7th and 8th grade string players to Symphony Day at the Grand River Center!
Students will come together for rehearsals and workshops with DSO musicians. The day culminates with a concert which the public is welcome to attend from 5-5:15 pm! We will also broadcast the concert live on Facebook.

This event is made possible through grant funding from the Dubuque Racing Association and James B. and Melita A. McDonough Foundation.

Dubuque Community School District, Dodgeville School District, Platteville School District
